channel.title: Changing cache? [PI]
channel.description:
Hiya, been a really long time since I've messed with RSPS, wanted to start with something basic, which is a Project Insanity running a 319 cache and gameframe. Now, I've seen tons of people do this and they say it's easy but I can't seem to find a tutorial. If anyone could walk me through it, even if it's just by text I'd really appreciate it.
Also when I open PI up in eclipse it gives me a socket error of some sort, and I know I'm setting it up correctly.
Thanks for looking.

item.title: Changing cache? [PI]
item.dc:creator: @sk8rdude461 sk8rdude461
item.description:
@sk8rdude461 wrote:

Socket error typically means that there is something already running on the port. Make sure you aren’t running the cmd and eclipse at the same time.
The rest is client sided and should be asked in that section.

Read full topic
